 Hey, probably when you were learning Python,

00:06:53.760 --> 00:06:55.400
 you're like, whoa, what's this percent thing?

00:06:55.400 --> 00:06:56.480
 And why did they choose percent?

00:06:56.480 --> 00:06:58.440
 And the answer is, that's what C chose.

00:06:58.440 --> 00:07:01.840
 And so, modulo is just percent in all these other languages

00:07:01.840 --> 00:07:03.880
 because they flipped a coin in C

00:07:03.880 --> 00:07:05.700
 and decided percent was modulo.

