 None and null are similar concepts, but quite different.

00:09:49.400 --> 00:09:51.920
 None in Python is its own type.

00:09:51.920 --> 00:09:55.740
 Null is the number zero.

00:09:55.740 --> 00:09:59.640
 That's cast to be a pointer to nothing.

00:09:59.640 --> 00:10:04.640
 And so, none is like specially marked empty.

00:10:04.640 --> 00:10:08.200
 Null is a zero.

