00:38:20.680 --> 00:38:24.320
 I mean, it might do something, it's just unexpected, right?

00:38:24.320 --> 00:38:26.080
 So there's no cleverness.

00:38:26.080 --> 00:38:28.300
 Now there might be some checking,

00:38:28.300 --> 00:38:29.960
 you might get a compiler warning that says,

00:38:29.960 --> 00:38:33.640
 how come it's an integer here, and it's a floating point here?

00:38:33.640 --> 00:38:36.200
 That will be dangerous, but it won't fix it for you,

00:38:36.200 --> 00:38:38.260
 and it doesn't automatically convert it.

00:38:38.260 --> 00:38:40.080
 Whereas if you did this in Python,

00:38:40.080 --> 00:38:41.580
 it would automatically convert.

00:38:41.580 --> 00:38:44.280
 So you have a far greater responsibility

00:38:44.280 --> 00:38:47.680
 to match your types up in C.

00:38:47.680 --> 00:38:53.160
 Things like return statement, pretty much functions the same.

00:38:53.160 --> 00:38:55.200
 That was, you know, the Python return statement

00:38:55.200 --> 00:38:57.160
 is an imitation of the C return statement.

00:38:57.160 --> 00:38:59.620
 You do have to declare your variable types

00:38:59.620 --> 00:39:02.020
 that aren't going to be used temporary inside the function.

00:39:02.020 --> 00:39:06.160
 Scope-wise, right, this C is not outside,

00:39:06.160 --> 00:39:09.160
 and we will see later when we get to the functions chapter

00:39:09.160 --> 00:39:12.240
 about external values and static values, et cetera.

00:39:12.240 --> 00:39:14.520
 But the default scoping is that any variable

00:39:14.520 --> 00:39:16.540
 that you declare inside of a function

00:39:16.540 --> 00:39:18.080
 only lives inside the function.

00:39:18.080 --> 00:39:21.360
 There is no A, B, or C in the main code,

00:39:21.360 --> 00:39:25.600
 and that's the same as how Python works.

00:39:25.600 --> 00:39:29.960
 Whew, that's a lot of Rosetta stone.

00:39:29.960 --> 00:39:32.040
 We talked about input-output, we talked about looping,

00:39:32.040 --> 00:39:33.240
 we talked about reading a file,

00:39:33.240 --> 00:39:34.320
 we've talked about strings,

00:39:34.320 --> 00:39:36.400
 which are really character arrays.

00:39:36.400 --> 00:39:38.560
 We've talked about float.

00:39:38.560 --> 00:39:41.360
 And later, later, later, later, later,

00:39:41.360 --> 00:39:42.640
 we're gonna learn a lot.

00:39:42.640 --> 00:39:45.680
 Chapters five and six are the crazy chapters,

00:39:45.680 --> 00:39:48.880
 but we're going to play with how would we implement

00:39:48.880 --> 00:39:51.600
 some of the things that Python strings,

00:39:51.600 --> 00:39:53.720
 lists, and dictionaries handle.

00:39:53.720 --> 00:39:55.980
 And before this course is over,

00:39:55.980 --> 00:40:00.080
 we're going to come back and get inside the mind

00:40:00.080 --> 00:40:04.880
 of what it would take to build Python using the C language.

00:40:04.880 --> 00:40:09.880
 So we'll see how alloc, structures, pointers, et cetera,

00:40:09.880 --> 00:40:15.560
 character arrays can be used to build string object,

00:40:15.560 --> 00:40:17.320
 list object, and dict object.

00:40:17.320 --> 00:40:19.800
 And that, to me, is the learning objective of this course,

00:40:19.800 --> 00:40:24.800
 is not so much how to code C because it's your job,

00:40:24.800 --> 00:40:29.240
 but what in C is necessary to make a higher level language

00:40:29.240 --> 00:40:34.000
 like Python or JavaScript or Java or C# work.

00:40:34.000 --> 00:40:36.120
 And we'll get to that before the end of the course.

00:40:36.120 --> 00:40:41.120
 It is a long course, and again, this was a long lecture.

00:40:41.120 --> 00:40:46.580
 This takes some time to absorb.

00:40:46.580 --> 00:40:49.860
 And just zooming through this,

00:40:49.860 --> 00:40:53.960
 you achieve nothing if you just do the homework

00:40:53.960 --> 00:40:56.920
 without understanding it, so take your time.

00:40:56.920 --> 00:40:58.560
 I put the lines in this lecture,

00:40:58.560 --> 00:41:02.400
 the lines of code are there very much on purpose.

00:41:02.400 --> 00:41:05.320
 Every single one is trying to teach something.

00:41:05.320 --> 00:41:09.260
 So I hope you'll take the time to learn all this material.

00:41:09.260 --> 00:41:10.100
 Cheers.

